  <mainDescription>This task defines the guided procedure for modelling a service composition.</mainDescription>
  <sections xmi:id="_XeblAFZ8Ed6NKeijDtiuXg" name="1. Create a VSCL Service Composition Diagram." guid="_XeblAFZ8Ed6NKeijDtiuXg"/>
  <sections xmi:id="_eBSOAFZ8Ed6NKeijDtiuXg" name="2. Define input and output of composition." guid="_eBSOAFZ8Ed6NKeijDtiuXg">
    <sectionDescription>Define the interface of the service composition by deciding the number of input and output parameters. In addition to that&#xD;
decide the type of each parametere, String, Integer, Complex Type or something else.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_f1zfoFZ8Ed6NKeijDtiuXg" name="3. Gather services to be used in the composition." guid="_f1zfoFZ8Ed6NKeijDtiuXg">
    <sectionDescription>Find the services you need for creating the composition. In most cases WSDL files are enough for identifying the different&#xD;
serivces.&lt;br /></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_jQPmMFZ8Ed6NKeijDtiuXg" name="4. Construct your composition." guid="_jQPmMFZ8Ed6NKeijDtiuXg">
    <sectionDescription>With use of the constructs of an Activity Diagram create your composition. Connect your services to Call Operation Actions&#xD;
by assigning one of the service operations to the operation slot in a Call Operation Action.&lt;br /></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <purpose>&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        To&amp;nbsp;model a service composition.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
